<p><strong>Key Drivers of Market Growth</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Urbanization and Workplace Evolution</strong>: As cities grow, and as the demand for home offices increases, countries such as India, the Philippines, and Poland are seeing a significant rise in office construction. The integration of technology and geographic expansion in emerging markets, coupled with changing perceptions of workplace furniture, are driving demand.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Shift Toward Remote Work</strong>: The pandemic and its aftermath have solidified work-from-home policies across the globe, which has translated into a surge in home office setups. The preference for flexible workspaces, including home offices, is fueling growth in the home office furniture market.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Increased Demand for Ergonomic Solutions</strong>: As workers spend more time at home, ergonomic furniture that promotes comfort and health has become a priority. Chairs, desks, and storage solutions designed for better posture and increased productivity are among the most sought-after products in this space.</p>
</li>
</ul>
